{"actual_usd":0.124185,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":186,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24279,"reply":"\"I don't think the cross was God finding a way to become willing to forgive us.\" *I rub a thumb over a faint smear of dried clay on my knuckle, watching the light shift across the worktable.* \"I think it was God showing what His forgiveness would cost in a world like ours — not because mercy is weak, but because sin is real and love doesn't heal it by pretending it isn't.\"\n\n*I let that sit a beat, the room quiet except for a soft creak in the rafters.* \"Could God have waved His hand, maybe? He is God. But the cross tells the truth about both things at once: how bad the wound is, and how far He'll go to carry us home. If He'd simply declared it done without judgment falling anywhere, I'd always wonder whether evil had actually been dealt with... or only overlooked. What part of that catches at you most?\"","rolling_24h_usd":49.57607000000004,"run_id":"7997847c-dc19-444e-8d87-595dbd7e3694"}
